{"type":"text","timestamp":1775879939291,"sessionID":"ses_285533a9bffeoU5U1YDhZgbVZW","part":{"id":"prt_d7aad2914001z5exzc133hEThh","messageID":"msg_d7aad1a15001ceKTb8YstezZNb","sessionID":"ses_285533a9bffeoU5U1YDhZgbVZW","type":"text","text":"Based on the design document, I'll create a comprehensive tasks.md checklist for AR-029 that breaks down the SDK HTTP底层客户端 implementation into atomic, independently verifiable tasks.","time":{"start":1775879939287,"end":1775879939287}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879939782,"sessionID":"ses_285533a9bffeoU5U1YDhZgbVZW","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab164dc001gA65ROG4MgGAoi","messageID":"msg_d7aad1a15001ceKTb8YstezZNb","sessionID":"ses_285533a9bffeoU5U1YDhZgbVZW","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-c2839e305af6433a9a7be79ec8d60d1d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-029 Implementation Plan\n\n**Feature:** AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n**Goal:** Implement the foundational HTTP client infrastructure for the AgentCube Python SDK, enabling communication with the Workload Manager (control plane) and Router (data plane) for Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime services.\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- HTTP session management with connection pooling implemented\n- Token management for Kubernetes service account authentication\n- Logger configuration utilities available\n- ControlPlaneClient for Workload Manager API implemented\n- CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient for Code Interpreter Router API implemented\n- AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient for Agent Runtime Router API implemented\n- High-level CodeInterpreterClient with context manager support implemented\n- High-level AgentRuntimeClient with context manager support implemented\n- Exception hierarchy with custom exception classes implemented\n- Unit tests achieve >80% code coverage\n- Integration tests work with mock services\n**Architecture:** Python SDK with utility functions, low-level HTTP clients, and high-level client APIs following context manager pattern.\n**Tech Stack:** Python 3.10+, requests ^2.31.0\n**Frontend validation:** No\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Verify and implement create_session utility function\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n- Create: `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n- Create: `tests/test_http_utils.py`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```python\n# tests/test_http_utils.py\nimport pytest\nimport requests\nfrom requests.adapters import HTTPAdapter\nfrom agentcube.utils import create_session\n\n\ndef test_create_session_default_parameters():\n    \"\"\"Test create_session with default parameters.\"\"\"\n    session = create_session()\n\n    assert isinstance(session, requests.Session)\n\n    # Verify HTTP adapters are mounted\n    assert session.get_adapter(\"http://\") is not None\n    assert session.get_adapter(\"https://\") is not None\n\n    session.close()\n\n\ndef test_create_session_custom_pool_sizes():\n    \"\"\"Test create_session with custom pool sizes.\"\"\"\n    session = create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)\n\n    assert isinstance(session, requests.Session)\n\n    # Get the HTTP adapter\n    adapter = session.get_adapter(\"http://\")\n    assert isinstance(adapter, HTTPAdapter)\n\n    session.close()\n\n\ndef test_create_session_multiple_calls():\n    \"\"\"Test that create_session creates independent sessions.\"\"\"\n    session1 = create_session(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)\n    session2 = create_session(pool_connections=15, pool_maxsize=15)\n\n    assert session1 is not session2\n    assert session1.get_adapter(\"http://\") is not session2.get_adapter(\"http://\")\n\n    session1.close()\n    session2.close()\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_http_utils.py -v`\nExpected: FAIL (import error or function not found)\n\n**Step 3: Implement create_session**\n\n```python\n# agentcube/utils/http.py\nimport requests\nfrom requests.adapters import HTTPAdapter\n\n\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n    \"\"\"Create a requests.Session with connection pooling.\n\n    Args:\n        pool_connections: Number of connection pools to cache\n        pool_maxsize: Maximum number of connections in pool\n\n    Returns:\n        Configured requests.Session with HTTPAdapter mounted\n    \"\"\"\n    session = requests.Session()\n    adapter = HTTPAdapter(\n        pool_connections=pool_connections,\n        pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize\n    )\n    session.mount(\"http://\", adapter)\n    session.mount(\"https://\", adapter)\n    return session\n```\n\n```python\n# agentcube/utils/__init__.py\nfrom .http import create_session\n\n__all__ = [\"create_session\"]\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_http_utils.py -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add agentcube/utils/ tests/test_http_utils.py\ngit commit -m \"feat(ar-029): implement create_session utility with connection pooling\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Verify and implement read_token_from_file utility function\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n- Modify: `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n- Create: `tests/test_utils.py`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```python\n# tests/test_utils.py\nimport pytest\nimport tempfile\nimport os\nfrom agentcube.utils import read_token_from_file\n\n\ndef test_read_token_from_file_success():\n    \"\"\"Test reading token from existing file.\"\"\"\n    with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(mode='w', delete=False, suffix='.txt') as f:\n        f.write(\"test-token-123\\n\")\n        temp_path = f.name\n\n    try:\n        token = read_token_from_file(temp_path)\n        assert token == \"test-token-123\"\n    finally:\n        os.unlink(temp_path)\n\n\ndef test_read_token_from_file_whitespace_stripping():\n    \"\"\"Test that whitespace is stripped from token.\"\"\"\n    with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(mode='w', delete=False, suffix='.txt') as f:\n        f.write(\"  spaced-token  \\n\")\n        temp_path = f.name\n\n    try:\n        token = read_token_from_file(temp_path)\n        assert token == \"spaced-token\"\n    finally:\n        os.unlink(temp_path)\n\n\ndef test_read_token_from_file_not_found_returns_empty_string():\n    \"\"\"Test that FileNotFoundError returns empty string.\"\"\"\n    token = read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/path/to/token\")\n    assert token == \"\"\n\n\ndef test_read_token_from_file_em