           mock_dp_instance = MagicMock()\n            mock_dp_instance.run_code.return_value = \"42\\n\"\n            mock_dp.return_value = mock_dp_instance\n\n            client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n                name=\"test-interpreter\",\n                router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n                session_id=\"existing-session-id\",\n            )\n\n            result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print(42)\")\n\n            assert result == \"42\\n\"\n            mock_dp_instance.run_code.assert_called_once()\n\n            client.stop()\n\n\ndef test_write_file_delegates_to_data_plane():\n    \"\"\"Test write_file delegates to data plane client.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.ControlPlaneClient\") as mock_cp:\n        mock_cp_instance = MagicMock()\n        mock_cp_instance.create_session.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n        mock_cp.return_value = mock_cp_instance\n\n        with patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n            mock_dp_instance = MagicMock()\n            mock_dp.return_value = mock_dp_instance\n\n            client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n                name=\"test-interpreter\",\n                router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n                session_id=\"existing-session-id\",\n            )\n\n            client.write_file(\"content\", \"/path/to/file.txt\")\n\n            mock_dp_instance.write_file.assert_called_once()\n\n            client.stop()\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py -v -k \"execute_command or run_code or write_file\"`\nExpected: FAIL (methods not found)\n\n**Step 3: Implement delegate methods**\n\n```python\n# Add to agentcube/code_interpreter.py\n    def execute_command(\n        self,\n        command: Union[str, list],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Execute command in Code Interpreter session.\n\n        Args:\n            command: Command string or list of arguments\n            timeout: Command timeout in seconds\n\n        Returns:\n            Command stdout output\n\n        Raises:\n            CommandExecutionError: If command exits with non-zero code\n        \"\"\"\n        return self.dp_client.execute_command(command, timeout)\n\n    def run_code(\n        self,\n        language: str,\n        code: str,\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Execute code in specified language.\n\n        Args:\n            language: Programming language (python, python3, py)\n            code: Code to execute\n            timeout: Execution timeout in seconds\n\n        Returns:\n            Code execution output\n        \"\"\"\n        return self.dp_client.run_code(language, code, timeout)\n\n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Write content to remote file.\n\n        Args:\n            content: File content as string\n            remote_path: Remote file path\n        \"\"\"\n        self.dp_client.write_file(content, remote_path)\n\n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Upload local file to remote path.\n\n        Args:\n            local_path: Local file path\n            remote_path: Remote file path\n        \"\"\"\n        self.dp_client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)\n\n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Download remote file to local path.\n\n        Args:\n            remote_path: Remote file path\n            local_path: Local file path\n        \"\"\"\n        self.dp_client.download_file(remote_path, local_path)\n\n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n        \"\"\"List files in remote path.\n\n        Args:\n            path: Remote path (default: \".\")\n\n        Returns:\n            Directory listing structure\n        \"\"\"\n        return self.dp_client.list_files(path)\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py -v -k \"execute_command or run_code or write_file\"`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add agentcube/code_interpreter.py tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py\ngit commit -m \"feat(ar-029): implement CodeInterpreterClient delegate methods\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 15: Verify and implement AgentRuntimeClient\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `agentcube/__init__.py`\n- Create: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n- Create: `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py\nimport os\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nimport pytest\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n\ndef test_agent_runtime_client_initialization():\n    \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient initialization.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_dp_instance = MagicMock()\n        mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n        mock_dp.return_value = mock_dp_instance\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            namespace=\"production\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            verbose=True,\n            timeout=180,\n            connect_timeout=10.0,\n        )\n\n        assert client.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n        assert client.namespace == \"production\"\n        assert client.router_url == \"http://router:8080\"\n        assert client.session_id == \"test-session-id\"\n\n        client.close()\n\n\ndef test_agent_runtime_client_with_existing_session_id():\n    \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient with existing session_id.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_dp_instance = MagicMock()\n        mock_dp.return_value = mock_dp_instance\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            session_id=\"existing-session-id\",\n        )\n\n        assert client.session_id == \"existing-session-id\"\n        mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.assert_not_called()\n\n        client.close()\n\n\ndef test_agent_runtime_client_context_manager():\n    \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient context manager support.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_dp_instance = MagicMock()\n        mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n        mock_dp.return_value = mock_dp_instance\n\n        with AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        ) as client:\n            assert isinstance(client, AgentRuntimeClient)\n\n        mock_dp_instance.close.assert_called_once()\n\n\ndef test_agent_runtime_client_invoke():\n    \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient invoke method.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_dp_instance = MagicMock()\n        mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n        mock_response = MagicMock()\n        mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\"}\n        mock_dp_instance.invoke.return_value = mock_response\n        mock_dp.return_value = mock_dp_instance\n\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        )\n\n        result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"test\"})\n\n        assert result == {\"result\": \"success\"}\n        mock_dp_instance.invoke.assert_called_once()\n\n        client.close()\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py -v`\nExpected: FAIL (import error)\n\n**Step 3: Implement AgentRuntimeClient**\n\n```python\n# agentcube/agent_runtime.py\nimport os\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\nfrom agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\nfrom agentcube.utils import get_logger\n\n\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Initialize Agent Runtime client.\n\n        Args:\n            agent_name: Agent name\n            namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n            router_url: Router URL (or ROUTER_URL env var)\n            verbose: Enable verbose logging\n            session_id: Existing session ID\n            timeout: Default request timeout\n            connect_timeout: Connect timeout\n        \"\"\"\n        self.agent_name = agent_name\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.router_url = router_url or os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\", \"\")\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.timeout = timeout\n        self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__)\n\n        self.dp_client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=self.router_url,\n            namespace=namespace,\n            agent_name=agent_name,\n            timeout=timeout,\n            connect_timeout=connect_timeout,\n        )\n\n        if session_id:\n            self.session_id = session_id\n        else:\n            self.session_id = self.dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()\n\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\":\n        return self\n\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n        self.close()\n\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None\n    ) -> Any:\n        \"\"\"Invoke agent with payload.\n\n        Args:\n            payload: Agent invocation payload\n            timeout: Request timeout (None for default)\n\n        Returns:\n            Agent response\n\n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If session_id not initialized\n            requests.exceptions.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n        \"\"\"\n        response = self.dp_client.invoke(self.session_id, payload, timeout)\n        return response.json()\n\n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close HTTP session and release resources.\"\"\"\n        self.dp_client.close()\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add agentcube/agent_runtime.py tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py\ngit commit -m \"feat(ar-029): implement AgentRuntimeClient\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 16: Run all unit tests and verify coverage\n\n**Files:**\n- None (verification task)\n\n**Step 1: Run all tests**\n\n```bash\npython -m pytest tests/ -v\n```\n\nExpected: All tests PASS\n\n**Step 2: Run tests with coverage**\n\n```bash\npython -m pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing\n```\n\nExpected: Coverage >80%\n\n**Step 3: Generate coverage report**\n\n```bash\npython -m pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=html\n```\n\n**Step 4: Review coverage report**\n\nOpen `htmlcov/index.html` in a browser and verify:\n- `agentcube/utils/` has >80% coverage\n- `agentcube/clients/` has >80% coverage\n- `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` has >80% coverage\n- `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` has >80% coverage\n- `agentcube/exceptions.py` has 100% coverage\n\n**Step 5: Fix any coverage gaps if below 80%**\n\nAdd tests for any uncovered code paths.\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add tests/\ngit commit -m \"test(ar-029): achieve >80% test coverage\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 17: Verify type checking with mypy\n\n**Files:**\n- None (verification task)\n\n**Step 1: Install mypy if not installed**\n\n```bash\npip install mypy\n```\n\n*