rom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_services():\n    \"\"\"Create mock Workload Manager and Router services.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.ControlPlaneClient\") as mock_cp:\n        with patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n            mock_cp_instance = MagicMock()\n            mock_cp_instance.create_session.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n            mock_cp_instance.delete_session.return_value = True\n            mock_cp.return_value = mock_cp_instance\n\n            mock_dp_instance = MagicMock()\n            mock_dp.return_value = mock_dp_instance\n\n            yield mock_cp_instance, mock_dp_instance\n\n\ndef test_end_to_end_code_interpreter_workflow(mock_services):\n    \"\"\"Test end-to-end Code Interpreter workflow.\"\"\"\n    mock_cp, mock_dp = mock_services\n\n    # Mock command execution\n    mock_dp.execute_command.return_value = \"42\\n\"\n\n    with CodeInterpreterClient(\n        name=\"test-interpreter\",\n        router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n        workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\"\n    ) as client:\n        # Execute command\n        result = client.execute_command([\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print(42)\"])\n        assert \"42\" in result\n\n    # Verify session cleanup\n    mock_cp.delete_session.assert_called_once()\n\n\ndef test_code_interpreter_session_reuse(mock_services):\n    \"\"\"Test Code Interpreter session reuse.\"\"\"\n    mock_cp, mock_dp = mock_services\n\n    # Mock operations\n    mock_dp.execute_command.return_value = \"output\"\n    mock_dp.write_file.return_value = None\n\n    with CodeInterpreterClient(\n        name=\"test-interpreter\",\n        router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n        session_id=\"existing-session-id\"\n    ) as client:\n        # Multiple operations\n        client.write_file(\"print(42)\", \"script.py\")\n        result = client.execute_command([\"python3\", \"script.py\"])\n        assert result == \"output\"\n\n    # Verify session was NOT deleted (it was provided)\n    mock_cp.delete_session.assert_not_called()\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/integration/test_agent_runtime_integration.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_router():\n    \"\"\"Create a mock Router service.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_dp_instance = MagicMock()\n        mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session-123\"\n        mock_response = MagicMock()\n        mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\", \"answer\": \"Paris\"}\n        mock_dp_instance.invoke.return_value = mock_response\n        mock_dp.return_value = mock_dp_instance\n\n        yield mock_dp_instance\n\n\ndef test_end_to_end_agent_invocation(mock_router):\n    \"\"\"Test end-to-end agent invocation workflow.\"\"\"\n    with AgentRuntimeClient(\n        agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n        namespace=\"default\",\n        router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n    ) as client:\n        result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is the capital of France?\"})\n\n        assert result[\"result\"] == \"success\"\n        assert \"Paris\" in result[\"answer\"]\n\n    # Verify session was closed\n    mock_router.close.assert_called_once()\n\n\ndef test_agent_runtime_multiple_invocations(mock_router):\n    \"\"\"Test multiple agent invocations with session reuse.\"\"\"\n    mock_router.invoke.return_value.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n\n    with AgentRuntimeClient(\n        agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n        router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n    ) as client:\n        # First invocation\n        result1 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"first\"})\n        assert result1[\"result\"] == \"ok\"\n\n        # Second invocation - should reuse same session\n        result2 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"second\"})\n        assert result2[\"result\"] == \"ok\"\n\n    # Verify bootstrap was called only once\n    mock_router.bootstrap_session_id.assert_called_once()\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run integration tests**\n\n```bash\npython -m pytest tests/integration/ -v\n```\n\nExpected: All integration tests PASS\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add tests/integration/\ngit commit -m \"test(ar-029): add integration tests with mock services\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 20: Create usage examples\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `examples/code_interpreter_basic.py`\n- Create: `examples/code_interpreter_file_operations.py`\n- Create: `examples/agent_runtime_basic.py`\n- Create: `examples/agent_runtime_session_reuse.py`\n\n**Step 1: Create basic CodeInterpreterClient example**\n\n```python\n# examples/code_interpreter_basic.py\n\"\"\"Basic CodeInterpreterClient usage example.\"\"\"\n\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\n\ndef main():\n    \"\"\"Demonstrate basic CodeInterpreterClient usage.\"\"\"\n    with CodeInterpreterClient(\n        name=\"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace=\"default\",\n        router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n        workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\"\n    ) as client:\n        # Execute a command\n        output = client.execute_command([\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('Hello, World!')\"])\n        print(f\"Command output: {output}\")\n\n        # Execute Python code\n        result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print(2 + 2)\")\n        print(f\"Code execution result: {result}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create file operations example**\n\n```python\n# examples/code_interpreter_file_operations.py\n\"\"\"CodeInterpreterClient file operations example.\"\"\"\n\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\n\ndef main():\n    \"\"\"Demonstrate file operations with CodeInterpreterClient.\"\"\"\n    with CodeInterpreterClient(\n        name=\"my-interpreter\",\n        router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n        workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\"\n    ) as client:\n        # Write a Python file\n        client.write_file(\"print('Hello from file!')\", \"/tmp/hello.py\")\n\n        # Execute the file\n        output = client.execute_command([\"python3\", \"/tmp/hello.py\"])\n        print(f\"Output: {output}\")\n\n        # List files\n        files = client.list_files(\"/tmp\")\n        print(f\"Files in /tmp: {files}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n```\n\n**Step 3: Create basic AgentRuntimeClient example**\n\n```python\n# examples/agent_runtime_basic.py\n\"\"\"Basic AgentRuntimeClient usage example.\"\"\"\n\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n\ndef main():\n    \"\"\"Demonstrate basic AgentRuntimeClient usage.\"\"\"\n    with AgentRuntimeClient(\n        agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n        namespace=\"default\",\n        router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n    ) as client:\n        # Invoke agent with a query\n        result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is the capital of France?\"})\n\n        print(\"Agent response:\")\n        print(result)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n```\n\n**Step 4: Create session reuse example**\n\n```python\n# examples/agent_runtime_session_reuse.py\n\"\"\"AgentRuntimeClient session reuse example.\"\"\"\n\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n\ndef main():\n    \"\"\"Demonstrate session reuse across multiple invocations.\"\"\"\n    with AgentRuntimeClient(\n        agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n        router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n    ) as client:\n        # Session is bootstrapped on first use\n        result1 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is 2 + 2?\"})\n        print(f\"Result 1: {result1}\")\n\n        # Same session is reused\n        result2 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is 3 + 3?\"})\n        print(f\"Result 2: {result2}\")\n\n        result3 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is 4 + 4?\"})\n        print(f\"Result 3: {result3}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n```\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add examples/\ngit commit -m \"docs(ar-029): add usage examples\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 21: Update documentation\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `README.md`\n- Create: `docs/code_interpreter_client.md`\n- Create: `docs/agent_runtime_client.md`\n\n**Step 1: Create main README**\n\n```markdown\n# AgentCube Python SDK\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK provides a high-level interface for interacting with AgentCube services, including Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime workloads.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install agentcube-sdk\n```\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Code Interpreter\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(\n    name=\"my-interpreter\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\"\n) as client:\n    # Execute a command\n    output = client.execute_command([\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print(42)\"])\n    print(output)\n```\n\n### Agent Runtime\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n) as client:\n    # Invoke agent\n    result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"Hello!\"})\n    print(result)\n```\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Required |\n|----------|-------------|----------|\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload Manager URL | No |\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Router URL | No |\n\n## Documentation\n\n- [CodeInterpreterClient Documentation](docs/code_interpreter_client.md)\n- [AgentRuntimeClient Documentation](docs/agent_runtime_client.md)\n\n## Examples\n\nSee the `examples/` directory for complete usage examples.\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create CodeInterpreterClient documentation**\n\n```markdown\n# CodeInterpreterClient Documentation\n\nThe CodeInterpreterClient provides a high-level interface for executing code and managing files in isolated Code Interpreter sessions.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(\n    name=\"my-interpreter\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\"\n) as client:\n    output = client.execute_command([\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print(42)\"])\n    print(output)\n```\n\n## Constructor Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `name` | str | \"my-interpreter\" | Session name |\n| `namespace` | str | \"default\" | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `ttl` | int | 3600 | Session time-to-live in seconds |\n| `workload_manager_url` | str \\| None | None | Workload Manager URL |\n| `router_url` | str \\| None | None | Router URL (required) |\n| `auth_token` | str \\| None | None | Authentication token |\n| `verbose` | bool | False | Enable verbose logging |\n| `session_id` | str \\| None | None | Existing session ID to reuse |\n\n## API Reference\n\n### `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n\nExecute a command in the Code Interpreter session.\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `command`: str or list - Command to execute\n- `timeout`: Optional[float] - Timeout in seconds\n\n**Returns:** str - Command stdout output\n\n**Raises:** `CommandExecutionError` - If command exits with non-zero code\n\n### `run_code(language, code, timeout=None)`\n\nExecute code in a specific language.\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `language`: str - Programming language (python, python3, py)\n- `code`: str - Code to execute\n- `timeout`: Optional[float] - Timeout in seconds\n\n**Returns:** str - Code execution output\n\n### `write_file(content, remote_path)`\n\nWrite content to a remote file.\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `content`: str - File content\n- `remote_path`: str - Remote file path\n\n### `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`\n\nUpload a local file to the remote session.\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `local_path`: str - Local file path\n- `remote_path`: str - Remote file path\n\n### `download_file(remote_path, local_path)`\n\nDownload a remote file to local path.\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `remote_path`: str - Remote file path\n- `local_path`: str - Local file path\n\n### `list_files(path=\".\")`\n\nList files in the remote path.\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `path`: str - Remote path (default: \".\")\n\n**Returns:** Dict - Directory listing\n```\n\n**Step 3: Create AgentRuntimeClient documentation**\n\n```markdown\n# AgentRuntimeClient Documentation\n\nThe AgentRuntimeClient provides a high-level interface for invoking agent runtime workloads through the Router service.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n) as client:\n    result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is the capital of France?\"})\n    print(result)\n```\n\n## Constructor Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | str | Required | Agent runtime name |\n| `namespace` | str | \"default\" | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `router_url` | str \\| None | None | Router URL (required) |\n| `verbose` | bool | False | Enable verbose logging |\n| `session_id` | str \\| None | None | Existing session ID to reuse |\n| `timeout` | int | 120 | Read timeout in seconds |\n| `connect_timeout` | float | 5.0 | Connect timeout in seconds |\n\n## API Reference\n\n### `invoke(payload, timeout=None)`\n\nInvoke the agent runtime with a payload.\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `payload`: Dict[str, Any] - JSON payload to send\n- `timeout`: Optional[float] - Timeout in seconds (overrides default)\n\n**Returns:** Dict[str, Any] - Response JSON\n\n**Raises:**\n- `ValueError` - If session_id is not initialized\n- `requests.RequestException` - If the request fails\n\n## Session Management\n\n### Automatic Session Bootstrap\n\nWhen `session_id` is not provided, the client automatically bootstraps a session ID from the Router:\n\n```python\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n# Session ID is bootstrapped on first use\nresult = client.invoke({\"query\": \"hello\"})\n```\n\n### Session Reuse\n\nYou can reuse an existing session by providing `session_id`:\n\n```python\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    session_id=\"existing-session-id\"\n)\n# Skips bootstrap, uses provided session ID\nresult = client.invoke({\"query\": \"hello\"})\n```\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add README.md docs/\ngit commit -m \"docs(ar-029): add comprehensive documentation\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 22: Final verification and cleanup\n\n**Files:**\n- None (verification task)\n\n**Step 1: Run all tests**\n\n```bash\npython -m pytest tests/ -v --cov=agentcube\n```\n\nExpected: All tests PASS with >80% coverage\n\n**Step 2: Run linting**\n\n```bash\nruff check agentcube/\n```\n\nFix any linting issues.\n\n**Step 3: Run type checking**\n\n```bash\nmypy agentcube/\n```\n\nExpected: No type errors\n\n**Step 4: Verify package builds**\n\n```bash\npython -m build\n```\n\nExpected: Build succeeds\n\n**Step 5: Update CHANGE.md**\n\nAdd entry for AR-029 implementation.\n\n**Step 6: Final commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add CHANGE.md\ngit commit -m \"chore(ar-029): final verification and cleanup\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis implementation plan breaks down AR-029 (SDK HTTP 底层客户端) into 22 atomic, independently verifiable tasks:\n\n1. **Implement create_session utility** - HTTP session management with connection pooling\n2. **Implement read_token_from_file utility** - Token management for K8s service accounts\n3. **Implement get_logger utility** - Logger configuration\n4. **Implement exception hierarchy** - Custom exception classes\n5. **Implement ControlPlaneClient initialization** - Control plane HTTP client setup\n6. **Implement ControlPlaneClient create_session** - Session creation method\n7. **Implement ControlPlaneClient delete_session** - Session deletion method\n8. **Implement CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient initialization** - Data plane client setup\n9. **Implement execute_command method** - Command execution\n10. **Implement file operations** - Write, upload, download, list files\n11. **Implement run_code method** - Code execution support\n12. **Implement AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** - Agent runtime HTTP client\n13. **Implement CodeInterpreterClient initialization** - High-level client setup\n14. **Implement CodeInterpreterClient delegate methods** - Command and code execution\n15. **Implement AgentRuntimeClient** - High-level agent runtime client\n16. **Run all tests with coverage** - Ensure >80% code coverage\n17. **Verify type checking** - Run mypy and fix type errors\n18. **Verify package builds** - Ensure package builds and installs correctly\n19. **Create integration tests** - Test end-to-end workflows\n20. **Create usage examples** - Provide example code\n21. **Update documentation** - Create comprehensive docs\n22. **Final verification** - Run all checks and cleanup\n\nEach task follows the TDD pattern:\n- Write comprehensive tests first\n- Implement minimal code to pass tests\n- Run tests to verify behavior\n- Commit changes\n\nThe implementation ensures:\n- HTTP session management with connection pooling\n- Token-based authentication support\n- Proper error handling and exception hierarchy\n- Context manager support for resource cleanup\n- High-level APIs for easy interaction with services\n- High test coverage and code quality\n- Comprehensive documentation and examples","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/python-sdk/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/python-sdk/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/python-sdk/tasks.md","time":{"start